        "cooked": "<p>I just did, thank you!</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox githubissue\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-iOS/issues/5945\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-iOS/issues/5945\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">github.com/signalapp/Signal-iOS</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"github-row\">\n  <div class=\"github-icon-container\" title=\"Issue\" data-github-private-repo=\"false\">\n\t  <svg width=\"60\" height=\"60\" class=\"github-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 14 16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z\"></path></svg>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-info-container\">\n    <h4>\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-iOS/issues/5945\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Status doesn't clear for others</a>\n    </h4>\n\n    <div class=\"github-info\">\n      <div class=\"date\">\n        opened <span class=\"discourse-local-date\" data-format=\"ll\" data-date=\"2025-01-23\" data-time=\"10:03:59\" data-timezone=\"UTC\">10:03AM - 23 Jan 25 UTC</span>\n      </div>\n\n\n      <div class=\"user\">\n        <a href=\"https://github.com/lajawi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">\n          <img alt=\"lajawi\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/9/d/9d3812767a548ba54e76d7bded8054a5f1a3ea5e.png\" class=\"onebox-avatar-inline\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-dominant-color=\"A6ADDB\">\n          lajawi\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"labels\">\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-row\">\n    <p class=\"github-body-container\">&lt;!-- This is a bug report template. By following the instructions below and fill<span class=\"show-more-container\"><a href=\"\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"show-more\">…</a></span><span class=\"excerpt hidden\">ing out the sections with your information, you will help the developers get all the necessary data to fix your issue.\nYou can also preview your report before submitting it. You may remove sections that aren't relevant to your particular case.\n\nBefore we begin, please note that this tracker is only for issues. It is not for questions, comments, or feature requests.\n\nIf you would like to discuss a new feature or submit suggestions, please visit the community forum:\nhttps://community.signalusers.org\n\nIf you are looking for support, please visit our support center:\nhttps://support.signal.org/\nor email support@signal.org\n\nLet's begin with a checklist: Replace the empty checkboxes [ ] below with checked ones [x] accordingly. --&gt;\n\n- [x] I have searched open and closed issues for duplicates\n- [x] I am submitting a bug report for existing functionality that does not work as intended\n- [x] This isn't a feature request or a discussion topic\n\n----------------------------------------\n\n### Bug description\nI’ve noticed that, if I clear my status and/or the emoji, it doesn’t clear said status for my contacts. Only if I change it does it update.\n\nI’ve been made aware of this issue, only roughly a year after I cleared my last status (which apparently was still showing for people I chat with).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n- Set a status\n- Check your status on another person's device\n- Clear your status again on your device\n- Check your status on another person's device again\n   - Status is still there (unwanted)\n\n**Actual result:** The previous status still shows up on other people's devices, even when you cleared it.\n\n**Expected result:** The status shouldn't show up anywhere after you've cleared it.\n\n### Screenshots\n\n\n\n### Device info\n\n**Device**: iPhone SE 3, iPhone 6s\n\n**iOS version**: iOS 18.2.1, iOS ~15\n\n**Signal version:** 7.42.1 (569), ???\n\n### Link to debug log\n\n\nhttps://debuglogs.org/ios/7.42.1/e59a93ee9a36f7c6c478ee02f7b11150e4a2ddbcfb0ae8506f6f2fd71052a441.zip\n\n&lt;!--  If this is a crashing bug, after filing this issue, email a copy of your latest crash report to support@whispersystems.org\n\nTo get a crash log:\n\n1. Go to the iOS Settings app.\n2. Go to Privacy.\n3. Go to Analytics or Diagnostics &amp; Usage.\n4. Select Analytics Data or Diagnostics &amp; Usage Data.\n5. Locate the .ips crash log for Signal.\n    The logs will be named in the format: Signal(DateTime).ips\n6. Select the desired Signal log.\n7.a iOS 11 users, tap the Share icon in the top right corner and jump to step 10.\n7.b iOS 9&amp;10 users, long press to see the option to highlight text and select the entire text of the log. It will end in EOF.\n8. Once the text is selected, tap Copy.\n9. Paste the copied text into an email.\n10. Send the email to support@signal.org with a subject like:\n  * \"iOS Crash Log: (your github issue)\"\n  * Example subject: iOS Crash Log: Crash on launch #111\n  * Example subject: iOS Crash Log: Crash when sending video #222\n--&gt;</span></p>\n  </div>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
